Mufalo Chitam, executive director of the Maine Immigrants’ Rights Coalition, which operates an online [resource hub](https://maineimmigrantrights.org/mirc-resource-hub/) and [hotline](https://www.pressherald.com/2025/10/27/maine-immigrant-advocacy-groups-launch-ice-activity-hotline-as-they-struggle-to-get-answers-on-arrests/) to report ICE activity, said her organization has been on high alert for 48 hours, preparing for a possible statewide response.

