Since the killing, [ICE protests have erupted](https://www.pressherald.com/2026/01/10/portland-protestors-join-in-national-anti-ice-rallies/) across the country, including in Maine.

In his statement, Dion said, “If you decide to protest or demonstrate, keep your efforts peaceful and consistent with the expectations for lawful behavior that we all share.”

